    process.exit(1);
  }
});
```

## Summary
The current implementation shows a pattern of poor secret management:
- Secrets are defined but not used
- Test secrets are committed to version control
- No proper loading mechanism is implemented

The best practice is to never commit any secrets (even test ones) to version control and use proper secrets management solutions for production applications.

